*Custom Exceptions:** Clear exception handling for transformation-related errors.\n- **Comprehensive Testing:** Unit tests covering built-in types and custom classes.\n\n## Installation\n\nYou can install Objectron via pip:\n\n```bash\npip install Objectron\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nSee the [Documentation](/docs/wiki/index.md) for detailed usage examples.\n\n## Contributing\n\nContributions are welcome! Please open an issue or submit a pull request for any improvements or bug fixes.\n\n## License\n\nThis project is licensed under the MIT License.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "Objectron.controllers", "documentation": ["Placeholder for controller implementations", "Future implementations can handle specific transformation scenarios", "or manage multiple objectrons"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "Objectron.wrappers", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "Objectron.wrappers.method_wrapper", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "method", "type": {"name": "Callable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Callable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Callable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Callable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["A decorator to wrap methods for logging or other purposes.\n\nArgs:\n    method (Callable): The method to wrap.\n\nReturns:\n    Callable: The wrapped method."]}], "variables": [{"name": "Objectron.wrappers.logger", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "Objectron.exceptions", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "Objectron.exceptions.TransformationError", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [{"name": "Objectron.exceptions.TransformationError.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "message", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Exception raised when an error occurs during object transformation."]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "Objectron", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "Objectron.ComplexProxy", "xref": {"fqname": "Objectron.proxy.ComplexProxy", "project": null}}, {"name": "Objectron.DictProxy", "xref": {"fqname": "Objectron.proxy.DictProxy", "project": null}}, {"name": "Objectron.DynamicProxy", "xref": {"fqname": "Objectron.proxy.DynamicProxy", "project": null}}, {"name": "Objectron.FloatProxy", "xref": {"fqname": "Objectron.proxy.FloatProxy", "project": null}}, {"name": "Objectron.FrozensetProxy", "xref": {"fqname": "Objectron.proxy.FrozensetProxy", "project": null}}, {"name": "Objectron.IntProxy", "xref": {"fqname": "Objectron.proxy.IntProxy", "project": null}}, {"name": "Objectron.Objectron", "xref": {"fqname": "Objectron.objectron.Objectron", "project": null}}, {"name": "Objectron.StrProxy", "xref": {"fqname": "Objectron.proxy.StrProxy", "project": null}}, {"name": "Objectron.TupleProxy", "xref": {"fqname": "Objectron.proxy.TupleProxy", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "Objectron.objectron", "documentation": ["Objectron Module\n\nThis module provides functionality to transform Python objects for tracking and\nmonitoring. It implements a proxy-based system that allows for dynamic attribute\naccess, method interception, and reference tracking across the entire object graph.\n\nKey Features:\n    - Object transformation and proxying\n    - Reference tracking and reshaping\n    - Support for both mutable and immutable types\n    - Class and instance wrapping capabilities"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "Objectron.objectron.T", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "Objectron.objectron.TransformedObject", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "Objectron.objectron.Objectron", "bases": ["ReferenceObjectron"], "methods": [{"name": "Objectron.objectron.Objectron.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Initialize a new Objectron instance.\n\nCreates an empty registry to track transformed objects and their proxies.\nThis ensures that the same object is always transformed to the same proxy."]}, {"name": "Objectron.objectron.Objectron.transform", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "value", "type": {"name": "object", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.object", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "TransformedObject", "xref": {"fqname": "TransformedObject", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Transform a Python object into its corresponding proxy object.\n\nThis method handles different Python types by creating appropriate\nproxy objects.\nFor built-in types, it uses specialized proxy classes\n(IntProxy, DictProxy, etc.).\nFor custom classes, it creates a dynamic proxy that preserves the\noriginal interface.\n\nArgs:\n    value (T): The object to transform. Can be of any Python type.\n\nReturns:\n    TransformedObject[T]: A proxy object that wraps the original value while\n                        maintaining its interface and adding\n                        tracking capabilities.\n\nExamples:\n    >>> objectron = Objectron()\n    >>> dict_proxy = objectron.transform({\"a\": 1})\n    >>> int_proxy = objectron.transform(42)\n    >>> list_proxy = objectron.transform([1, 2, 3])"]}, {"name": "Objectron.objectron.Objectron.wrap_class", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cls", "type": {"name": "type", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.type", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "type", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.type", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Create a proxy subclass that wraps the given class.\n\nThis method creates a new class that inherits from the original class\nand adds proxy functionality. All instances of the wrapped class will\nautomatically be proxied.\n\nArgs:\n    cls (Type[T]): The class to wrap with proxy functionality.\n\nReturns:\n    Type[T]: A new class that inherits from the original and includes\n            proxy capabilities.\n\nExample:\n    >>> @objectron.wrap_class\n    >>> class MyClass:\n    >>>     def __init__(self):\n    >>>         self.value = 42"]}, {"name": "Objectron.objectron.Objectron.reshape_references", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "original", "type": {"name": "object", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.object", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "transformed", "type": {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Update all references to the original object with the transformed version.\n\nThis method scans the entire object graph to find references to the original\nobject and replaces them with references to the transformed proxy object.\n\nArgs:\n    original (T): The original object whose references need to be updated.\n    transformed (Any): The transformed proxy object to replace references with.\n\nRaises:\n    TransformationError: If an error occurs during reference reshaping."]}, {"name": "Objectron.objectron.Objectron.add_class", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cls", "type": {"name": "Type", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Type", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "T", "xref": {"fqname": "T", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Register a class for transformation tracking.\n\nThis method wraps the class and makes it available globally for transformation.\n\nArgs:\n    cls (Type[T]): The class to add to the transformation registry."]}, {"name": "Objectron.objectron.Objectron.add_instance", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "instance", "type": {"name": "object", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.object", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Register an instance for transformation tracking.\n\nThis method transforms the instance and adds it to the transformation registry.\n\nArgs:\n    instance (object): The instance to add to the transformation registry."]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["A class that transforms Python objects to enable tracking and monitoring.\n\nThe Objectron class serves as the main entry point for object transformation.\nIt maintains a registry of transformed instances and provides methods to transform\nvarious Python types into their corresponding proxy objects.\n\nAttributes:\n    _instances (dict): A registry mapping object IDs to their transformed proxies.\n                     This ensures consistency in transformation across the\n                     object graph.\n\nExample:\n    >>> objectron = Objectron()\n    >>> obj = {\"key\": \"value\"}\n    >>> transformed = objectron.transform(obj)\n    >>> transformed.new_key = \"new_value\"  # Dynamic attribute assignment\n    >>> print(transformed)  # DictProxy({'key': 'value', 'new_key': 'new_value'})"]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "Objectron.proxy", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "Objectron.proxy.T", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "Objectron.proxy.ReferenceObjectron", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "Objectron.proxy.ReferenceObjectron.transform", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "value", "type": {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Forward declaration for type hinting."]}, {"name": "Objectron.proxy.DynamicProxy", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "Objectron.proxy.DynamicProxy.__new__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "obj", "type": {"name": "T", "xref": {"fqname": "T", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "objectron", "type": {"name": "ReferenceObjectron", "xref": {"fqname": "Objectron.proxy.ReferenceObjectron", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "DynamicProxy", "xref": {"fqname": "Objectron.proxy.DynamicProxy", "project": null}, "params": [{"name": "T", "xref": {"fqname": "T", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "Objectron.proxy.DynamicProxy.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "obj", "type": {"name": "T", "xref": {"fqname": "T", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "objectron", "type": {"name": "ReferenceObjectron", "xref": {"fqname": "Objectron.proxy.ReferenceObjectron", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xre